File: PetroSA will start hearings into the unauthorised sale of South Africa's crude oil reserves. JOHANNESBURG - PetroSA begin hearings into the unauthorised sale of South Africa’s crude oil reserves on Monday. The sale of 10.3-million barrels happened between December 2015 and March 2016. READ: Burning oil tanker off Sri Lanka leaves kilometre-long slick This was during Tina Joemat-Petersen’s tenure as energy minister, who at the time, denied the sale. She told Parliament that it was instead a strategic rotation of oil resources. The Strategic Fuel Fund commissioned a forensic report, while the Hawks also probed the matter.